AGI - At least three people were killed and wounded in an avalanche in Zermatt>, one of the main ski destinations in the Swiss Alps: The local police reported it. The avalanche, which was resumed by some witnesses, occurred shortly after 14:00 local time (13:00 GMT) in an off-piste area of the Riffelberg ski resort, on a day of great affluence for Easter holidays. The authorities of the Canton of Valais had raised the avalanche alarm in the area due to the abundant snowfalls of the last days and strong winds.
&nbsp;
The Valais cantonal police did not provide the nationality of the three victims. For the moment the research is suspended and a new evaluation will be taken tomorrow morning. The Riffelberg area is known by skiers who practice the off-piste, or outside the track. The avalanche danger in today's day in that area was grade 4 on a scale ranging from 1 to 5. Following the abundant snowfall of the past hours the danger of avalanches on the Alps is between 'strong' and 'marked'. In Switzerland during the next winter season, 14 people were killed by slavine on twelve total accidents.

